<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[96,1535,1329,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[96,225,1329,1359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Placement in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[504,593,1329,1359]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrus">
<emphasis box="[504,593,1329,1359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">nigrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1896" box="[843,987,1329,1359]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[843,987,1329,1359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pachomius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indicated by the presence of both a sclerotized (spike-like) lateral subterminal apophysis (LSA) and a well-developed proximal retrolateral lobe (pRL) of the male pedipalp. In this group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1908" box="[833,995,1404,1434]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Phiale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehmanni">
<emphasis box="[833,995,1404,1434]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. lehmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Caporiacco, 1947)" baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1947" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrus">
<emphasis box="[1411,1533,1404,1434]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. nigrus</emphasis>
(Caporiacco, 1947)
</taxonomicName>
by its more slenderer LSA and embolus, narrower tegulum with a more slender pRL, and RTA with a wider base (
<figureCitation box="[474,634,1480,1509]" captionStart="Figures 1-3" captionStartId="2.[96,188,847,871]" captionTargetBox="[96,1537,172,806]" captionTargetId="figure-100@2.[534,1018,167,814]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1-3. Pachomius lehmanni (Strand, 1908), male holotype (SMF 2377-141). 1, Left pedipalp, ventral view, detail of the bulb. 2, Same, retrolateral view. 3, Dorsal view. Abbreviations: Cy = cymbium; e = embolus; pRL = proximal retrolateral lobe of the tegular basal division; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; Spe = spermophore." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5093278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5093278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1-2</figureCitation>
; see Figures 
<quantity box="[808,888,1480,1509]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" metricValueMax="2.286" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6-9 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; A. D. Brescovit &amp; A. A. Lise" box="[895,1116,1480,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="376 - 381" refId="ref1777" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S., A. D. Brescovit and A. A. Lise. 2007. On the taxonomy of some neotropical species of jumping spiders described by Caporiacco (Araneae, Salticidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia 24: 376 - 381." type="journal article" year="2007">Ruiz et al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[96,1533,1553,1659]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[96,242,1553,1584]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Comments.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[315,436,1555,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">holotype</typeStatus>
male that was examined is well preserved and has a brown carapace with lateral and longitudinal stripes of white hairs, and eyes on black marks. The abdomen has an anterior and lateral white stripe, two transverse light-brown lines, and two lateral and posterior white spots (
<figureCitation box="[1309,1426,1630,1659]" captionStart="Figures 1-3" captionStartId="2.[96,188,847,871]" captionTargetBox="[96,1537,172,806]" captionTargetId="figure-100@2.[534,1018,167,814]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1-3. Pachomius lehmanni (Strand, 1908), male holotype (SMF 2377-141). 1, Left pedipalp, ventral view, detail of the bulb. 2, Same, retrolateral view. 3, Dorsal view. Abbreviations: Cy = cymbium; e = embolus; pRL = proximal retrolateral lobe of the tegular basal division; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; Spe = spermophore." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5093278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5093278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figure 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[96,1535,1703,1846]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[96,257,1703,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution</emphasis>
. The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[350,439,1703,1733]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrus">
<emphasis box="[350,439,1703,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">nigrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1896" box="[687,831,1703,1733]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[687,831,1703,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pachomius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of two species from northern South America (
<figureCitation box="[239,369,1742,1771]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="2.[96,175,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[96,1536,995,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-137@2.[96,1536,995,1771]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 4. Known distribution of the nigrus species group of Pachomius (Salticidae: Salticinae: Aelurillini: Freyina) in northern South America. Map by Mapswire.com (https://mapswire.com) used and modified under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) License." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5093280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5093280/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1908" box="[425,589,1741,1771]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Phiale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehmanni">
<emphasis box="[425,589,1741,1771]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. lehmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[833,962,1742,1771]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[990,1078,1742,1771]" country="Colombia" name="Cauca" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Cauca</collectingRegion>
), known from an elevation of approximately 
<quantity box="[305,416,1780,1809]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="m" value="1750.0">1750 m</quantity>
above sea level. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[668,788,1778,1808]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrus">
<emphasis box="[668,788,1778,1808]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. nigrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1116,1780,1809]" name="Guyana" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1134,1359,1780,1809]" country="Guyana" name="Potaro-Siparuni" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Potaro-Siparuni</collectingRegion>
) and French Guiana (Saint-Élie) from an elevation between 
<quantity box="[731,881,1817,1846]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="m" value="210.0" valueMax="270.0" valueMin="150.0">150-270 m</quantity>
above sea level.
</paragraph>
